<subSubSection box="[151,540,1051,1076]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1051,1327]" box="[151,540,1051,1076]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,540,1051,1076]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<number box="[151,188,1051,1076]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.1">2.1</number>
. Complex 
<taxonomicName box="[314,540,1051,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectipennis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[314,540,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Isophya rectipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1051,1327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Characteristic with more primitive morphology and song in comparison with the other representatives of the group. Slender species. 
<collectingCountry box="[350,406,1124,1148]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora are without ventral spines. CuP is weak and short, CuP and CuA are widely separated. The venation of female tegmen is clearly parallel or to some extent reticulate (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1367,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis box="[1208,1367,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">I. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The ovipositor is short (
<quantity box="[374,474,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9 mm</quantity>
). The song (at least in 
<taxonomicName box="[739,887,1197,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectipennis">
<emphasis box="[739,887,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">I. rectipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) consists of short syllables arranged in phrases. The cerci are elongated, slender. The complex includes two species having widely isolated ranges of distribution— 
<taxonomicName box="[151,301,1269,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectipennis">
<emphasis box="[151,301,1269,1292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">I. rectipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(E Balkans and NW 
<collectingCountry box="[558,692,1268,1292]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Asia 
<taxonomicName box="[620,692,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ulmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">Minor</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[761,922,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis box="[761,922,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">I. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[940,1040,1268,1292]" name="Lebanon" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1101,1164,1268,1292]" name="Syria" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Syria</collectingCountry>
; see Sevgili and Heller 
<number box="[151,212,1303,1327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2003.0">2003</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
